A man walks into a bar and asks the bartender for a glass of water. The bartender pulls out a gun and points it at the man. The man says "Thank you" and walks out. What happened?
The man had hiccups. The bartender scared him to cure them. He no longer needed the water.
+The Funeral Crush
A girl is at her mother's funeral and meets a handsome stranger she has never seen before. She can't get his number before he leaves. A few days later, her sister dies. The police suspect it was murder. Who killed the sister?
The girl killed her sister. She was hoping the stranger would show up at another family funeral, since she didn't know how else to find him.
+The Snowman's Clues
A carrot, a scarf, and five pieces of coal are found lying on a neighbor's lawn. Nobody put them there deliberately, but there is a perfectly logical reason. What is it?
Children built a snowman that has since melted. The items were the snowman's nose, scarf, and buttons.
