The numbers correspond to elements on the periodic table by atomic number: Iron(26)-Lithium(3)-Iodine(53)... spelled out, the sequence spells N-I-C-O-L-A-S — the name of the murderer.
+The One-Way Ticket
A couple went on a climbing trip but only the husband came back. He told police his wife slipped and fell off a cliff. The local detective called the travel agent and immediately arrested the husband. What did the agent say?
The husband had only booked a one-way ticket for his wife. He had always planned to return alone.
+The Murder at School
On the first day of school, a teacher is found murdered. Police question four suspects. The landscaper said he was mowing the lawn. The math teacher said he was giving a mid-year exam. The basketball coach said she was running drills. The principal said she was in her office. Who did it?
The math teacher. You cannot give a mid-year exam on the first day of school.
+The Monopoly Man
A man is pushing his car down the street. He stops in front of a hotel and immediately declares himself bankrupt. What is going on?
He is playing Monopoly.
