A truck driver is going down a one-way street in the wrong direction. A police officer drives right past him and doesn't stop him. Why?
The truck driver is walking, not driving.
+The Upside-Down Flag
A Japanese ship was caught in a storm. Afterward, the captain was found dead. The engineer said he was fixing signals, the cook said he was managing wine barrels, the wife went to her cabin, and the maid said she was fixing the upside-down flag. Police arrested the maid immediately. Why?
Japan's flag is a red circle on a white background — it looks the same right-side up or upside down. The maid was lying.
+The Lucky Plane Ticket
Helen never thought that her decision to travel by plane would save her life. How?
Helen's house was destroyed while she was away on her flight. If she had stayed home, she would have been killed.
+The Desert Package
A man is found dead in an open field. Next to him is an unopened package. There are no other footprints or marks in the area. What happened?
The package is an unopened parachute. It failed to deploy.
+The Casino Thief
On a dark night, a casino owner invited friends over. They placed money on the table just before the lights went out. When the lights returned, the money was gone. The owner put a rooster inside an old rusty bucket and told everyone to touch it in the dark, claiming the rooster would crow when the thief touched it. The rooster never crowed, yet the owner still found the thief. How?
By touching the rusty bucket, everyone got rust on their hands. The thief was too scared to touch the bucket in case the rooster crowed — so their hands had no rust on them at all.
+The Bald Man
A man was walking down the street when it started raining. He had no umbrella and no hat, yet not a single hair on his head got wet. How?
The man was completely bald.
+The Train Runner
A man was walking along a railway bridge when he heard a train approaching from behind. The train was travelling at 100 km/h. To survive, he ran toward the train instead of away from it. He made it off the bridge just in time. Why did he run toward it?
He was more than halfway across the bridge. Running forward toward the train was faster than running back the longer distance behind him.
+The Locked Office
A man is found dead in his locked office. There is no weapon, no signs of struggle, and only a sealed envelope on his desk. How did he die?
He licked a poisoned envelope seal before locking himself in. The poison was absorbed through his tongue.
+The First Floor Jumper
A man who lives in a 30-story building decides to jump out of his window. He survives with no injuries. How?
He jumped out of a first-floor window.